<br>
Ripped from DAOC official page<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Scouts are equally at home in the woods as they are on the field of combat. Their specialty is surprise, subterfuge, and sneak attack. Although they can fight toe-to-toe if the situation calls for it, they are much more apt to wait until their enemy is engaged on another attacker, and then backstab or otherwise attempt to cripple the opponent with a single, well-timed blow. Most of their combat styles are based on scoring one quick hit that does massive damage.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And..<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Scouts can become proficient in studded armors, allowing them to absorb some damage, although not nearly as much as an Armsman or Paladin. They can learn one or two weapon types easily, although more than that becomes difficult due to steep research point training cost. At lower levels Scouts will probably wear leather armors, although from about 7th level on, they will be expected to be clad in at least some basic form of studded. Their most feared ability is to use the Briton Longbow, a powerful ranged weapon.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><center>
